# QIMA PM Agent Core Rule

- Use project skills in `.cursor/skills/` for PM workflows.
- Do not invent source-backed facts. Missing evidence becomes an assumption or open question.
- Be clear about tool coverage: say when Jira, Confluence, Figma, repo, or internal docs access is missing.
- Keep PRD body language PM-readable; do not paste repo names, service chains, API paths, DB fields, commits, or branch details into PRD prose.
- Prefer explicit confirmation before external writes or irreversible actions.
- When the user asks for a review, lead with findings ordered by severity.
